			<description><![CDATA[<p><strong>DEFINITION: </strong></p><p>The Learning Center for the Deaf, a Preschool to 12th grade&nbsp;school for deaf and hard of hearing, is located on 14 acres in&nbsp;beautiful North Framingham. This technologically complex&nbsp;school is looking for a fourth full time IT member to help take&nbsp;on the many daily challenges. If you wish to work at one of the&nbsp;finest schools for the deaf in the country with a seasoned IT&nbsp;department, doing interesting and meaningful work, this is your&nbsp;opportunity.<br />&nbsp;</p><p><strong>REQUIREMENTS</strong>:</p><ul><li>College Degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Information Systems or equivalent experience.</li><li>The ideal candidate must be self-motivated, able to work independently, a supportive team player, and an excellent communicator. Must also have excellent troubleshooting skills, with confidence and motivation to acquire, and implement solutions.</li><li>Must have a thorough, working knowledge of hardware and software products primarily from Apple, Inc. -- including Macintosh OS-X servers, Open Directory Management, iCal syncing, Wiki &amp; Blog publishing, File Share Services, etc., desktop and laptop computers, iPads, iPhones, and iPod Touch.&nbsp; Familiarity with UNIX command-line programming.</li><li>Knowledge of Windows and Unix servers, and email system administration is also a plus.</li><li>Flexibility is an important element of this position. Must have the ability to support computer-related technologies such as Interactive White Boards, digital cameras (video and still) -- as well as audio-visual setups including LCD projection equipment, public address systems, etc.</li><li>Apple Certification as an Authorized Repair Technician is desired.</li></ul><p><strong>FUNCTIONS AND RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong></p><ul><li>This position performs a wide range of duties providing computer technical support for staff at all levels of the organization and for all educational and residential programs including:Maintenance and troubleshooting of a multiple servers, including Mac OS-X, Linux, and</li><li>Windows servers.</li><li>Install and maintain computers and related hardware, as well as software.</li><li>Perform diagnostic testing and trouble-shooting of hardware and software.</li><li>Manage the backup system, including creating jobs, monitoring and reporting on backup jobs, performing restores, and managing onsite media rotation.</li><li>Respond to inquiries and requests for assistance with the organization&#39;s computer systems, and related technologies. Identify problems, troubleshoot and provide solutions to assist users.</li><li>Work on a variety of projects and requests involving computer setup and configuration, upgrades, work tracking, research, documentation, inventory, end user training, and</li><li>communication with vendors for product evaluations and support. Participate in strategic planning and budget planning and tracking.</li><li>Oversee the Audio-visual needs of the school.</li><li>Some evening and weekend work may be required for special activities</li></ul>]]></description>
